benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Retrieve payment tags

covered: Valid Request coverage: TC01 (no params), TC02 (includedDeleted), TC03 (pluginProperty), TC04 (audit FULL), TC05 (all params) demonstrate successful retrieval under varied parameter combinations; TC06 covers empty tag set; TC07/TC20 cover not-found scenarios; TC09 covers missing authentication; TC10 covers invalid audit values; TC11 covers ignoring unexpected query parameters; TC12 covers performance under load; TC14 covers regression for deleted tags; TC15/TC16 cover security (SQL injection, XSS); TC17/TC18 cover edge cases (max pluginProperty entries, large payload); TC19/TC22/TC23 cover state variation, backward compatibility, and accessibility; TC21 covers recovery from transient network issues; TC24 covers internal server error scenarios.
Query Parameters and data variety: TC01–TC05 exercise different parameter combinations (including includedDeleted, pluginProperty, audit) and TC11 confirms extra params are ignored.
Error handling and resilience: TC07/TC09/TC10/TC13/TC20/TC24 test 404/401/400/503/500 responses across not found, auth, invalid input, dependency failure, and server error scenarios.
Security coverage: TC15 (SQL injection) and TC16 (XSS) scenarios are included.
Performance and accessibility: TC12 tests performance under load; TC23 tests accessibility of the response structure.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination handling for large datasets when a payment has many tags.
Caching Behavior: No tests verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related cache validation behavior.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or 429 responses under rapid successive requests.
Authorization depth: No explicit test for 403 Forbidden when user lacks required permissions (beyond 401).
recommendations: Add pagination-focused tests to validate paging, page size limits, and correct aggregation when tag lists are large.
Add tests to validate caching headers and semantics (ETag/Cache-Control) and potential cache invalidation scenarios.
Add rate limiting/throttling tests (e.g., multiple rapid requests leading to 429).
Add a dedicated 403 Forbidden scenario to verify proper handling when user has insufficient permissions.
